entry.def: Things that are interchangeable can be exchanged with each other without it making any difference.

means.word_mean: 1. of or relating to or suggestive of complementation;
2. (mathematics, logic) such that the arguments or roles can be interchanged;

sentences.sentence: "the arguments of the symmetric relation, `is a sister of,' are interchangeable"

means.word_mean: 3. capable of replacing or changing places with something else;
